<section id="work" class="alt-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>What I Work On</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">🏗️</div>
        <h3>Azure Landing Zones</h3>
        <p>
          End-to-end ALZ Corp deployments with Terraform and Bicep. 135+ automated
          checklist validations via Azure Resource Graph. Security and compliance
          built in from day one, not bolted on.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">☸️</div>
        <h3>AKS &amp; Kubernetes</h3>
        <p>
          AKS Automatic clusters with ALZ Corp networking. BYO VNet, Application
          Gateway for Containers, NGINX, Istio — multiple ingress and egress patterns
          documented with full Terraform parity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔒</div>
        <h3>IaC Security</h3>
        <p>
          Terraform modules built to run inside ALZ Corp landing zones: no public IPs,
          central firewall egress, managed identity everywhere. PSRule and azqr
          integrated into CI pipelines.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">🤖</div>
        <h3>AI-Assisted Development</h3>
        <p>
          Multi-agent GitHub Copilot workflows for code review, issue triage, and
          PR management. Squad patterns that keep AI output reviewable and
          production-quality.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">🏃</div>
        <h3>GitHub Runners</h3>
        <p>
          GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners with Azure VNet integration, Container
          Apps, and ALZ Corp firewall egress. GHE.com EU data residency patterns.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-icon">📊</div>
        <h3>Azure Assessment</h3>
        <p>
          Automated Azure assessments bundling azqr, PSRule, AzGovViz, and ALZ graph
          queries into a single portable runner with unified JSON and HTML reports.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
